cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new class of codes for distributed matrix multiplication and discusses their properties in terms of distance separability and decoding complexity. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper is specifically focused on distributed matrix multiplication and proposes codes to handle stragglers in the distributed setting. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the encoding and decoding complexity of the proposed codes and compares them to other existing codes. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the use of codes for distributed matrix multiplication in the context of networked systems. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper emphasizes the numerical stability of the proposed codes and compares them to other existing codes in terms of reconstruction error.
